title: Pieces  the puzzle
author: madison
text: a picture is worth a thousand words but a puzzle is worth more the smooth pieces and cookie cutters that lay scattered on the kitchen floor are threads of beads and words similar in every person's tale each piece to be placed side by side will set a special ship to sail a puzzle is more than pieces,  a puzzle is more than games; every puzzle piece will shift through great measures,  words,  and names secretly lurking in the shadows or fearlessly placed in the center once pieces are set,  they can't be moved and time can't be reentered on odd occasions pieces are lost in the murkiness of doubt and despair and some may never be retrieved of this you must beware however,  pieces painted black are very few each piece of golden light was made by love for you so,  look upon your many pieces of pure hope undefeated and trust,  one day,  that your puzzle will be completed.

title: The Mountain House
author: madison
text: in my mountain house,  the cold breeze,   looming mountains,  trapped in,   completly free,   to write,  to daydream,  idle around.  the pond,   the hills,   the grass,   the fields,  green grass surroundes me,  making me feel free as i can be,   the purple mountains,  with mist skirting around their tops,   trapping me in,  making me feel secluded and alone,  a good alone,  i write,  i feel,  i live there.  i can think and dream,  and run,  and be,   i can hole myself in my room,  with my paper,  my pen,  my mind,  or run free up and down the grassy hills with no a thought in sight.  to be there is refreshing,  to leave your cares behind,  travel to your inside,  step into your mind.  connect with yourself,  with the ones that are there with you is to be renewed,   happy,  peaceful,  carefree,   deep,   my mind is alone,  but myself and a pen is all i need.  you may think a mountain house can't have this affect on me,   but if you think that,  you have never been in a place with such peace,  where you can be deep,  be yourself,  and be free,   in the mountain house,   i can be,   completely free.

title: THE GURDIAN ANGEL
author: manny
text: i was in a coma for about 2 â½ weeks the reason was that i had a bacterium on my foot,  my mother was sitting next to me in the visitorâ’s chair  she spent the whole night with me,  and to her it felt like year.   while i was lying there with all of the tubes going into my body,  my mom was just there lying down with tears dripping down her cheek.  she just wanted to be god and just stop me from suffering,  she said that when she went to sleep that night she had a dream,  her dream was that she saw me lying there and she said that she saw an angel,   that angel was holding my hand my mother said she woke up right there,  when she turned to look at me she saw a big shine just fly out the window.  the next two days after that i woke from the coma,  when they checked my knee with a hammer,  had my reflexes.  when my mother told me all of this that same night i prayed to god and i thanked him,  for what he has done,  he sent a guardian to look over me.

title: Farewell
author: marissa
text: midst the path of life there are many fears,  and yet companions are there to be found,  a heartfelt friend is assured to be near,  when our troubled hearts seem to scratch the ground.   from heights of the earth to depths of the sea,  you'll hear the echo of a loving friend,  these tidal waves crash like sweet harmony,  in plaid songs of love there comes no end.   what if your echo is not answered back? the looking-glass shows only your dull face,  the estatic face of your friend it lacks,  there's a vacant spot for them in that place.   we speak the words of farewell to a friend,  sorrow seeps in,  for you know its the end.

title: Eyes
author: megz
text: happy as they look,  these eyes are really sad.  hidden by a book,  because of a father being bad.   the mouth says she's fine,  but her eyes cannot lie.  searching for a sign,  they turn up towards the sky.   then on the next day,  you see those eyes again.  though they quickly turn away,  they're filled with tears and pain.   a nose has bled,  the eyes been beat.  stomach not fed,  two torn and swollen feet.   you help your friend,  her eyes so grateful.  assuring it's the end,  making them be faithful.   if a friend is abused,  look into their eyes.  you can tell that they've been used,  if their laughs are truly cries.   get them help fast,  their eyes will tell you to.  your friendship will be tight and last,  and they'll know your heart is true.   dedicated to dessi vencoon and all other children who have to live with abusive parents who neglect and treat them poorly,  who can only make their children feel unwanted and worthless even though they truly are not.   hearts all over the world are with you.

title: Reflection on a Dragon's Wing
author: megz
text: flying high he can see you.  you're below and behind,  not knowing he's approaching.  the dragon turns so slowly it seems motionless.  you lay your eyes upon him and start to run.  too late,  you see your reflection on his wing.   lower he flies,  drawing nearer.   running fast,  you flee.  the dragon wants food and is determined.  you look back and begin to scream.  too late,  you no longer see your reflection on his wing.

text: on one friday night i was walking outside.  the thunder howled and the rain poured,  i walked down mulberry street but couldn't open my door.  the trees swayed and the leaves rustled i was terrified and began to hustle.  i ran back up the road to my neighbor's house.  i found my dad but not his spouse.  he handed me keys so i could get into the door,  but i dropped the keys and they landed on the floor.  i picked them up and ran down the street and on my front porch i found a monster,  he really gave me the creeps.  he began to chase me and i ran into the house then he came in and slept on the couch. i woke up the next morning to see if he was still there.  i found out i was dreaming and i didn't really care.

title: A River
author: melissa
text: a river   alone  that is how i feel  i am separated  from everything around me.    today,  i looked out the window  and across the hudson river.   i saw flocks of white seagulls  and a single bluebird.    the river is like  mush moving along  so silently without noise.    there is a large chunk of ice floating off to the side  of the river  on that side,  the water is  all clear with no slush.    i look at it and it seems  very much like me.   separated,  isolated,   away from all the warmth and fun.    the slush on the other  side is everyone else  in the school  around me.    but for some reason,   they're not really there.   they're dim and fading  like some far away  land or memory  of what used to be there.    i look at the seagulls  i imagine some are just  teachers,   cheering me up  and making me feel  better about who i am.    others are classmates  performing rare acts  of kindness for me.   but they are just  classmates.   i try to look at them as  friends,   it never works.    but there is a bluebird.   it flies across the river  and visits the isolated ice.   it stays breifly.    soon,  it spreads it's wings  and takes flight.   and then,  it is gone  and again,  i am alone.    the bluebird is all i  really look forward to  it is one of a kind.   it never fails me.    it's my sunshine  my shield  my hope  if it ever fails,   my hope shall,  too.    the sky will grow dark  and my sheild will be gone.   i shall plummet into  misery and sadness.    for i shall only be wearing a mask  in a costume  concealed in the darkness  a shadow of who i really am or was.    now i stand up  look around me  i am not really seeing anything  as i appear to.   then,  i opened my eyes  opened my eyes  and for the first time  i saw.

title: Gracie
author: monica
text: her ears are like socks,  that droop to the ground.  every few steps she trips and falls,  sprawled all around.   but,  when i rub them for her,  my dog moans with pleasure.  then she licks my face,  with a smile i can't measure.   her eyes are like rain drops,  falling to the ground.  they make her look sad,   when she is happy,  looking all around.   she will look at you,  with those little drops,  you can't help but pet her,  and when you decide to stop,  she moans and groans for more.   she runs and plays,   when i am near her.  when i throw a ball,  she gets it,   i cheer for her,  and see her fall.   she gets back up,  and runs to me with glee.  she drops the ball,  i cheer for her and pet her,  and she licks me.

title: Friends

title: The Menacing Lion
author: morgan
text: the lion roared,  as i walked through the jungle.  he snarled while i watched in horror.  my brother was gone,  now ripped to shreds.  nothing was left of him,  not even his head.  i mourned for days,  weeks and months.  while the lion still stalked those who had stolen his lunch.  my mom was next,  my sister then my dad.  i was afraid that if i watched,  i would become so terribly sad.  so i sheilded my eyes,  for the lion frightened me.  now all i could do,  was sit and cry.  i knew i was going to be eaten,  it was only a matter of time.  i knew i was going to be beaten,  but i drifted to sleep as silent as a mime.  i never woke up from the deep sleep,  for the lion had gobbled me up.

title: Anatomy of a Couch Potato
author: nathaniel
text: welcome,  all,  to idaho,  where every couch potato grows.  a safari we will all go on,  exploring this adult,  named ron.   just to give you all a scare,  look at this hypnotic stare.  he watches tv day and night.  i hope this didn't give y'all a fright.   just a glance at his unshaven face,  will clue you in on his mom's disgrace.  his razor sits lonely by his sink,  because mobility is the missing link.   do not gawk at his enormous weight.  trust me,  his stomach carries too much freight.  jelly doughnuts did the trick.  no wonder he doesn't have a chick.   fungus keeps the remote in his hand,  but don't touch,  it feels like burnt sand.  orange,  yellow,  green,  and blue,  the plant life keeps on changing hue!  this b. o.  is getting toxic,   no destinkum,  wow,  that's sick! ''stink's'' not in his vocabulary,  so let's get a move on,  this is scary!  be appalled at these rolls of belly,  watch,  they wiggle,  just like jelly! he needs to buy a longer shirt.  with that bellybutton,  no eyes should flirt!  please do not lay eyes,  on things as thick as these thighs.  cellulite is his closest friend,  and they will not part until the end.   lastly,  the amorphous derriere,  which is treated with the utmost care.  i hear that it once crushed a moose,  and sadly,  its body lays lifelessly loose.   i hope this trip to idaho,  has taught you something you should know.  lots of tv is a growing fad,  and if you end up like him,  well that's too bad.
